            "creation_date": 1380365496,
            "body": "<p>The trick used here is called <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/anonymousclasses.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">anonymous classes<\/a>. Basically, you are creating a object of a new anonymous class that implements <code>Runnable<\/code>. <\/p>\n\n<p>The better example would be this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Thread t = new Thread(new Runnable(){ \n   @Override\n   public void run() {\n       // Code here\n   }\n});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19066111,
            "question_id": 19066006
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/VxHRi.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 1639157,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1511951,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1511951/steve-benett",
                "reputation": 12933,
                "display_name": "Steve Benett",
                "accept_rate": 77
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1380370342,
            "creation_date": 1380365578,
            "body": "<p><strong>We can create a reference of an interface but not object<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>That's not true. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ClassA classa = new ClassA(); \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This will make a new instance for ClassA, while <code>classa<\/code> is the reference.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>But how can we pass new Runnable() to the Thread constructor<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Thread t = new Thread(new Runnable(){});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This will make an instance of a Thread, where <code>t<\/code> is the reference. The new Runnable(){} is called an <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/355167/how-are-anonymous-inner-classes-used-in-java\">anonymous class<\/a>. Because an instance is created, the reference is passed to the constructor, but you can't refer to this one later in the code. <\/p>\n\n<p>But with this line you should get a compile error. You have to override the run method.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Thread t = new Thread(new Runnable(){\n    @Override\n    public void run(){\n    }\n});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19066126,
            "question_id": 19066006,
            "last_edit_date": 1495541005
        }
